A security officer was robbed and killed in Emona, Tongaat, on Tuesday afternoon. According to Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA), who were flagged down by one of the security officers, the officer and his colleague were guarding the Emona reservoir, when three people entered the premises and held them up. The two officers were allegedly robbed off their firearms and cellphones. The attackers fired three shots and fled on foot. One of the officers sustained a gunshot wound to the back and was declared dead by RUSA members. Police are investigating further.